quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  11,24,"The likeness of the two parties is as the man blind and deaf, and the man who sees and hears; are they equal in likeness? Will you not remember"
  11,25,"And We sent Noah to his people: 'I am for you a warner, and a bearer of good tidings"
  11,26,Serve you none but God. I fear for you the chastisement of a painful day
  11,27,"Said the Council of the unbelievers of his people, 'We see thee not other than a mortal like ourselves, and we see no? any following thee but the vilest of us, inconsiderately. We do not see you have over us any superiority; no, rather we think you are liars"
  11,28,"He said, 'O my people, what think you? If I stand upon a clear sign from my Lord, and He has given me mercy from Him, and it has been obscured for you, shall we compel you to it while you are averse to it"
  11,29,"O my people, I do not ask of you wealth for this; my wage falls only upon God. I will not drive away those who believe; they shall surely meet their Lord. But I see you are an ignorant people"
  11,30,"O my people, who would help me against God, if I drive you away"
  11,31,"Will you not remember? I do not say to you, \"I possess the treasuries of God\"; I know not the Unseen; and I do not say, \"I am an angel.\" Nor do I say to those your eyes despise, \"God will not give them any good\"; God knows best what is in their hearts. 'Surely in that case I should be among the evildoers"
  11,32,"They said, 'Noah, thou hast disputed with us and make much disputation with us. Then bring us that thou promisest us, if thou speakest truly"
  11,33,"He said, 'God will bring you it if He will; you cannot frustrate Him"
  11,34,"And my sincere counsel will not profit you, if I desire to counsel you sincerely, if God desires to pervert you; He is your Lord, and unto Him you shall be returned"
  11,35,"Or do they say, 'He has forged it'? Say: 'If I have forged it, upon me falls my sin; and I am quit of the sins you do"
  11,36,"And it was revealed to Noah, saying, 'None of thy people shall believe but he who has already believed; so be thou not distressed by that they may be doing"
  11,37,"Make thou the Ark under Our eyes, and as We reveal; and address Me not concerning those who have done evil; they shall be drowned"
  11,38,"So he was making the Ark; and whenever a council of his people passed by him they scoffed at him, He said, 'If you scoff at us, we shall surely scoff at you, as you scoff"
  11,39,"and you shall know to whom will come a chastisement degrading him, and upon whom there shall alight a lasting chastisement"
  11,40,"Until, when Our command came, and the Oven boiled, We said, 'Embark in it two of every kind, and thy family -- except for him against whom the word has already been spoken and whosoever believes.' And there believed not with him except a few"